@node Information "Information"
I couldn't find a lister for .GB carts which handled a whole directory,
so I decided to create a small project for myself to:

1) Improve my programming skills.

2) Allow me to distribute carts programmed by @{"Peter Gordon" LINK Greets}.

This program simply lists Nintendo gameboy cartridge files (.GB) in a
nice list so that you can swap with friends easily etc.
@endnode
@node Requirements "Requirements"
You shouldn't need much to run GBlist. A few things are:

 - An Amiga
 - A bit of free mem
 - Some Gameboy emulator carts

I'm not sure if any particular Kickstart is needed. I would appreciate
it if someone mailed @{"me" LINK Credits} with info on whether it worked on WB2/1.3.

GBlist has been successfully tested on:

A1200/KS 39.106/1.1GB HD/18MB RAM/Apollo 33Mhz 68040
A1200/KS 39.106/3.2GB HD/18MB RAM/Apollo 50Mhz 68060
@endnode
@node Installation "Installation"
Copy the guide & executable to anywhere you wish (I recommend "GBlist"
goes in your C: directory).
@endnode
@node Usage "Usage"
The following CLI arguments can be used with the program:



    GBlist

    or

    GBlist ?


 --- Displays basic template



    GBlist file.gb

    or

    GBlist ram:t/motocros.gb


 --- Displays info on a single .GB cart



    GBlist ALL


 --- Scans current directory and lists out all files. Be warned that
     no checking of .GB files is included yet! Any non-gb cart files
     will display rubbish in the "proper" cartname box!


If you want to save your text file out as something, then you'll have to
redirect the output of the program to a file, like this:



    GBlist >ram:gblist.txt ALL

    or

    GBlist >ram:gblist.txt ram:t/motocros.gb
@endnode
@node Bugs "Bugs"
Although my code is (was) pretty messy, I have not come across any bugs
or crashes. If you do, then please mail @{"me" LINK Credits} with exact
information on the bug you encountered, your system setup and any other
programs you have running in the background.
@endnode
